
xdg-open image.jpg
Opens the file with the default image viewer for your desktop environment.	

eog image.jpg
Eye of GNOME - a simple image viewer for GNOME desktop.	

feh image.jpg
A lightweight image viewer for X11. (You may need to install it using your package manager.)	

display image.jpg
Part of ImageMagick - a powerful image manipulation tool that can also display images.	

imgcat image.jpg
A command from iTerm2 that can display images directly in the terminal (works in compatible terminal emulators).	

fbi -a image.jpg
A framebuffer image viewer for Linux (works from the console).	
